authorizeDotnsController(address).details: Only the store owner can grant this role.      This role does not grant write access by itself; the address must also be authorized via `authorizeStore`.

params.controllerAddress: The address to mark as DotNS controller.

authorizeStore(address).details: Only the store owner can authorize new addresses.

returns._0: The stored IPFS URI, or an empty string if none exists.

getValueFor(address,bytes32).details: Allows reading any user's stored data regardless of the caller.

params.user: The address whose storage to query.

returns._0: The stored IPFS URI, or an empty string if none exists.

getValues().details: Returns values in the order they were added. May include duplicates if setValue was called multiple times.

returns._0: An array of all IPFS URIs stored by the caller.

returns.exists: True if the key has a non-empty value.

params.storeAddress: The address to check authorization status.

returns.authorized: True if the address is authorized.

isDotnsController(address).details: DotNS controllers may cause `(user, key)` writes via `setValueFor` to become permanently locked.

returns.isController: True if the address is a DotNS controller.

params.user: The user namespace owner of the key.

returns.locked: True if the key is locked permanently.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setValue(bytes32,string).details: Keys are scoped to msg.sender to prevent collisions across users.

params.key: The unique identifier for the stored value.

setValueFor(address,bytes32,string).details: Only authorized contracts can call this function. Keys are scoped to the specified user.If the caller is a DotNS controller, the key may be locked permanently as part of the write.

params.key: The unique identifier for the stored value.
params.user: The address whose storage will be modified.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unauthorizeDotnsController(address).details: Only the store owner can revoke this role.      Revoking does not unlock existing locked keys.

params.controllerAddress: The address to unmark as DotNS controller.

unauthorizeStore(address).details: Only the store owner can revoke authorizations.

authorizeDotnsController(address).notice: Marks an address as a DotNS controller for locking semantics.

authorizeStore(address).notice: Authorizes an address to call setValueFor on behalf of users.

deleteValue(bytes32).notice: Delete a value associated with a key from caller's storage.

getValue(bytes32).notice: Retrieve the IPFS URI for a given key from caller's storage.

getValueFor(address,bytes32).notice: Retrieve the IPFS URI for a given key from a specified user's storage.

getValues().notice: Retrieve all stored values for the caller.

hasValue(bytes32).notice: Check if a key has a stored value in caller's storage.

isAuthorized(address).notice: Check if an address is authorized to write on behalf of users.

isDotnsController(address).notice: Check if an address is marked as a DotNS controller for locking semantics.

isLocked(address,bytes32).notice: Check if a `(user, key)` pair is permanently locked.

setValue(bytes32,string).notice: Store or update an IPFS URI under a given key for the caller.

setValueFor(address,bytes32,string).notice: Store or update an IPFS URI under a given key for a specified user.

unauthorizeDotnsController(address).notice: Removes DotNS controller status from an address.

unauthorizeStore(address).notice: Revokes authorization for an address to call setValueFor.
